description: This file defines the interface for the CCSP CWMP Stun Manager API, including function prototypes for creation, removal, enrollment, and initialization of the stun manager object. It is a header file specifying exported functions and constants relevant to the STUN (Session Traversal Utilities for NAT) management in the CCSP framework.

methods.name: CcspCwmpCreateStunManager
methods.description: Creates and returns a handle to the CCSP CWMP STUN Manager, given context handles.

methods.name: CcspCwmpStunmoCreate
methods.description: Creates an instance of the CCSP CWMP STUN Manager object with provided context handles.

methods.name: CcspCwmpStunmoRemove
methods.description: Removes and cleans up the CCSP CWMP STUN Manager object identified by the handle.

methods.name: CcspCwmpStunmoEnrollObjects
methods.description: Enrolls necessary objects for the CCSP CWMP STUN Manager operation.

methods.name: CcspCwmpStunmoInitialize
methods.description: Initializes the CCSP CWMP STUN Manager object.
